==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bumblebee
<hw>Bum"ble*bee`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>bumblen</ets> to make a humming noise (dim. of <ets>bum</ets>, v.
i.) + <ets>bee</ets>. Cf. <er>Humblebee</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large bee of the genus <gen>Bombus</gen>, sometimes called
<altname>humblebee</altname>; -- so named from its sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ There are many species. All gather honey, and store it
in the empty cocoons after the young have come out.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bumblepuppy</ent>⟦br⟧
